@node MAIN "Welcome"

@{fg shine}PaperBox@{fg text}

Welcome to PaperBox. With PaperBox, you can create realtime rendered boxes.

  @{"About PaperBox        " link ABOUT}
  @{"Requirements          " link REQUIREMENTS}
  @{"Usage                 " link USAGE}
  @{"Create your own boxes " link CREATEYOUROWNBOXES }


@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

@{fg shine}Requirements@{fg text}

Minimum system conifguration is:

- Amiga with 68060 CPU
- AmigaOS 3.0 or better
- StormMesa 3.0 or better
- Warp3D

You can get StormMesa and Warp3D from @{"Aminet" System "OpenURL http://main.aminet.net"}.


@endnode
@node USAGE "Usage"

@{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}

To view the Example files, just doubleclick their icons.
You can also start PaperBox form CLI by typing

PaperBox <Boxfile>

where <Boxfile> is the Boxfile to load.

You can switch the animation on and of using the menu entry "Toggle Animation" from the pulldown menu.
Use the cursor keys to rotate the box.


@endnode
@node CREATEYOUROWNBOXES "Create your own boxes"

@{fg shine}Create your own boxes@{fg text}

To create your own box, you need 6 texture files - one for each site
of the box. File format is 24 Bit BMP uncompressed. Other file formats
are not supported. Minimum texture size is 64x64 pixels.

Then you have to make a boxfile using a texteditor.
The first line in the boxfile are the dimensions of the box
in centimeters. The first value is the width, the second is the height
and the third is the depth of the box.
The following 6 lines are the paths of the textures for each side.
Take a look an the example files in directory data!


@endnode



